1
00:09:32,344 --> 00:09:34,096
Stop him!
拦住他!

2
00:09:37,424 --> 00:09:41,019
(RASPING WHISPER) Hunt that man! He must not escape!
去找他！不能让他逃走！

3
00:09:41,304 --> 00:09:43,977
Can we not help them? We can use the Tardis!
我们不能帮助他们吗？我们可以用 TARDIS!

4
00:09:44,044 --> 00:09:48,196
To go to the moon? We'd probably overshoot by a few million years!
到月球去吗？我们可能跑偏一百万年！

5
00:09:48,364 --> 00:09:50,355
Yes, or by a few million miles!
是的, 或者是一百万英里！

6
00:09:50,524 --> 00:09:53,596
I'm afraid the Tardis is not suited to short-range travel.
恐怕 TARDIS 不适合短途

7
00:09:53,764 --> 00:09:55,573
Still, I think we should help them if we can.
我仍然觉得我们应该尽我们所能帮助他们

8
00:09:55,744 --> 00:09:58,133
- Aye.  - Yes.
- 对    - 是

9
00:10:00,984 --> 00:10:05,243
- Still, I think I could get your rocket to the moon.
- You?
- 我仍然觉得我可以把你的火箭弄到月球上去  - 你？

10
00:10:05,304 --> 00:10:09,399
Yes, I have considerable experience in space travel, and so have my two companions.
是的, 在太空旅行方面, 我有相当丰富的经验, 我这两位同伴也是

11
00:10:09,464 --> 00:10:10,855
Doctor, that's splendid! Thank you!
博士, 那太棒了！谢谢你！

12
00:10:11,024 --> 00:10:15,717
- But the rocket is not ready!
- Perhaps you overestimate the difficulty.
- 但火箭条件还不成熟  - 也许你高估了问题了难度

13
00:10:15,984 --> 00:10:18,657
How much more work is required?
需要多少工作量？

14
00:10:18,824 --> 00:10:21,896
It needs fuel and a complete computerised check.
需要燃料, 还需要用电脑进行一次完全的检查

15
00:10:22,064 --> 00:10:25,181
- I can order that.
- No! I would not allow it! The risk is too great!
- 这我可以安排  - 不！我不允许！风险太大了

16
00:10:25,344 --> 00:10:26,335
If there was some other way,
如果有其它的法子

17
00:10:26,504 --> 00:10:29,302
- Believe me, I wouldn't even consider such a risk!
- No!
- 相信我, 我也不会考虑这么高风险的方法  - 不行

18
00:10:30,044 --> 00:10:32,281
<i>(COMPUTER) Commander Radnor</i>
Radnor 指挥官

19
00:10:35,004 --> 00:10:36,483
Radnor. Go ahead.
我是 Radnor, 继续

20
00:10:36,644 --> 00:10:39,363
<i>T-Mat receptions - New York, Moscow, Tokyo -</i>
各 T-Mat 接收站 - 纽约, 莫斯科, 东京

21
00:10:39,524 --> 00:10:41,961
<i>express great concern over continued hold-up.</i>
都对持续停运表达的严正关切

22
00:10:42,224 --> 00:10:46,137
<i>Medical shipments and food awaiting transit to Asiatic centres.</i>
大批医疗用品和食物亟待传输到亚洲中心

23
00:10:46,304 --> 00:10:49,774
<i>Position desperate, Calcutta. Instructions awaited.</i>
fixme

24
00:10:51,224 --> 00:10:54,660
- That's your answer!
- Well, we want to help, as I said!
- 那就是你的答案！  - 我们的确想帮忙, 我说过了

25
00:10:54,824 --> 00:10:57,213
You don't what you're doing! It's suicide!
你不明白你在做什么！这是自杀！

26
00:10:57,384 --> 00:11:00,660
Listen, if this fault lasts much longer,
听着, 如果这个故障继续往下拖着

27
00:11:00,824 --> 00:11:05,181
there's going to be worldwide chaos, and world population is at stake.
就会带来全世界的混乱, 所有地球人都受影响

28
00:11:05,344 --> 00:11:08,939
Infallible T-Mat, putting the world in jeopardy (?)
不倒的 T-Mat, 把全世界推向了危机！

29
00:11:09,104 --> 00:11:10,856
All right, I admit it.
好吧, 我承认

30
00:11:11,024 --> 00:11:13,492
Now this man has to risk his life to get you out of trouble!
现在这个人不得不押上自己的性命来解决你的麻烦

31
00:11:13,664 --> 00:11:17,259
No, not for me, for thousands of people all over the world
不, 不是为我, 是为了全世界成千上万的人

32
00:11:17,424 --> 00:11:20,177
who will die if we don't take this risk!
我们不冒这个险他们就会死

33
00:11:21,784 --> 00:11:25,299
I'm sorry but I've got no alternative.
很抱歉我没有其他方案

34
00:11:25,464 --> 00:11:27,898
- Miss Kelly.  - Sir.
- Kely 小姐  - 头儿

35
00:11:28,064 --> 00:11:31,136
I want all technical personnel working on this.
我要所有的技术人员都来搞这个

36
00:11:31,304 --> 00:11:34,137
I want that rocket prepared for launching!
我要这架火箭可以发射！

37
00:11:34,304 --> 00:11:36,295
Yes, Commander.
是, 指挥官

38
00:11:39,024 --> 00:11:42,016
We'd be grateful for your help.
对于你的帮助, 我们很感激

39
00:11:42,184 --> 00:11:45,893
If that rocket's to reach the moon safely, you'll need more than my help - you'll need a miracle!
要让那个火箭能安全到达月球, 你需要的不只是我的帮助 - 你需要一个奇迹！

40
00:11:55,784 --> 00:11:59,663
(RASPING WHISPER) Continue the search!
继续搜寻!

41
00:11:59,824 --> 00:12:01,815
He must not escape!
不能让他逃走！

42
00:12:01,984 --> 00:12:07,581
(HISSING, LABOURED BREATHING)

43
00:12:12,924 --> 00:12:15,313
- Commander.
- Yes, Miss Kelly?
- 指挥官  - 什么事, Kelly 小姐？

44
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:18,556
Do you think it's wise letting these people crew the rocket?
你觉得这样明智吗, 让这些人坐火箭过去

45
00:12:18,724 --> 00:12:21,236
Wise? No, of course it is not wise. But what's the alternative?/?
明智？不, 当然不明智．但没有其它办法了啊

45
00:12:21,724 --> 00:12:23,236
We gave up training astronauts years ago.
我们在多年以前就不再训练宇航员了

46
00:12:23,304 --> 00:12:26,514
- But Who are they?
- Some of Eldred's crazy friends, I imagine,
- 但他们都是什么人？  - Eldred 的一些疯朋友吧, 我猜

47
00:12:26,684 --> 00:12:30,518
- but the man who calls himeself the Doctor said he knows this space travel.
- How can you be sure?
- 但那个自称博士的人说他懂太空旅行  - 你能确信吗？

48
00:12:30,684 --> 00:12:34,154
You weren’t at the briefing, He and the girl know more about space flight than Eldred.
做简报的时候你不在．他和那个女孩儿在太空飞行方面比 Eldred 懂得多

49
00:12:34,324 --> 00:12:37,634
- What about the boy?
- Yes, I'm not sure about him.
- 那那个男孩儿呢  - 是, 我对他不太有把握

50
00:12:38,604 --> 00:12:41,597
(RASPING WHISPER) The emergency link with Earth,
跟地球的紧急连接

51
00:12:41,664 --> 00:12:43,758
- is it ready yet?
- I've nearly finished.
- 好了没有？  - 我快完成了

52
00:12:43,824 --> 00:12:46,636
- Do not make any mistakes!
- I'm not an expert!
- 不要出任何问题！  - 我不是个专家！

53
00:12:46,704 --> 00:12:48,695
- But you will do it?
- Yes!
- 但你能做吗？  - 是的！

54
00:12:49,784 --> 00:12:53,743
Commander, I think I should go as crew on the rocket.
指挥官, 我觉得我应该也到火箭上去

55
00:12:54,104 --> 00:12:57,219
Don't be ridiculous, you're too valuable here!
别傻了, 你在这里太重要了！

56
00:12:57,284 --> 00:12:59,752
How can T-Mat be repaired if I'm not there?
如果我不上去, T-Mat 怎么能修好呢？

57
00:12:59,924 --> 00:13:03,519
- What about one of the technicians who was already over there?
- Osgood's dead.
- 已经在那边的技术人员都不行吗？  - Osgood 已经死了

58
00:13:04,724 --> 00:13:09,195
- Yes, well, what about Fewsham?
- He's incapable of doing it! I think I should go!
- 是, 但是 Fewsham 怎么样？  - 他没有这个能力！我觉得我应该去！

59
00:13:09,364 --> 00:13:13,152
No! You're the only one who really understands T-Mat.
不, 你是唯一真正懂 T-Mat 的人

60
00:13:13,324 --> 00:13:15,554
I can't have you risking your life!
我不能让你拿你的性命去冒险！

61
00:13:15,724 --> 00:13:18,192
But yet you are perfectly prepared to allow them to risk theirs!
但你却允许他们拿性命去冒险！

62
00:13:18,364 --> 00:13:21,063
Don't worry, Miss Kelly we'll be perfectly all right!
别担心, Kelly 小姐, 我们会完全没事的！

63
00:13:22,884 --> 00:13:26,397
But I don't see what good just this emergency link can be.
但我看不出这个紧急连接能有什么用

64
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:29,017
Even if you had a gigantic army of warriors,
就算你有一只庞大军队, 全都是勇士

65
00:13:29,184 --> 00:13:32,017
you couldn't send them all to conquer Earth.
你也不能把他们都送过去征服地球

66
00:13:32,184 --> 00:13:34,778
(RASPING WHISPER) We do not need an army.
我们不需要一直军队

67
00:13:34,944 --> 00:13:37,139
Earth will be ours for the taking...
地球会是我们的...

68
00:13:37,304 --> 00:13:40,774
(HISSING BREATHING) ..very soon!
...很快就是！

69
00:13:46,744 --> 00:13:48,735
- Doctor...  - <i>Yes?</i>
- 博士...  - 什么事？

70
00:13:48,904 --> 00:13:52,260
Final check on procedure after you land.
最后核对一遍你着陆后的程序

71
00:13:52,424 --> 00:13:55,814
<i>Yes, I know we're to re-establish video link with the Earth.</i>
似的, 我知道我们要重新建立跟地球的视频连接

72
00:13:55,984 --> 00:13:57,463
That's right.
对的

73
00:13:57,624 --> 00:13:59,615
When we can see what's wrong,
一旦我们看出是什么地方出了问题

74
00:13:59,784 --> 00:14:03,094
you can do the rest under Miss Kelly's supervision.
剩下的事你们就可以在 Kelly 小姐的指导下完成了

75
00:14:03,264 --> 00:14:05,619
<i>Right. We're ready when you are.</i>
对．你们准备好了我们就发射了

76
00:14:07,284 --> 00:14:08,717
<i>12...</i>

77
00:14:08,884 --> 00:14:10,317
<i>10...</i>

78
00:14:10,484 --> 00:14:12,998
nine...eight...seven...
9...8...7...

79
00:14:13,164 --> 00:14:16,713
..six...five...four...three...
..6...5...4...3...

80
00:14:16,884 --> 00:14:19,000
..two...one.
..2...1.

81
00:14:22,764 --> 00:14:26,040
(HISSING, LABOURED BREATHING)

82
00:14:27,124 --> 00:14:28,603
It's done.
搞定了

83
00:14:28,764 --> 00:14:32,737
- The emergency link will work now.
- Excellent!
- 紧急连接可以工作了  - 非常好！

84
00:14:32,754 --> 00:14:36,030
- What are you going to do?
- Do not ask questions!
- 你打算做什么？  - 不许提问！

85
00:14:37,194 --> 00:14:39,124
Activate the link.
激活连接

86
00:14:40,294 --> 00:14:43,092
- On receive only.
- Receive?
- 设定为仅仅接收  - 接收？

87
00:14:43,654 --> 00:14:45,451
But aren't you going to send...?
但你们不是要传送...？

88
00:14:45,614 --> 00:14:47,923
Activate the link on receive at once!
将连接设置为仅接收, 立刻！

89
00:14:48,094 --> 00:14:51,986
- (KELLY) You've double-checked everything?
- <i>Yes, the fault is definitely on Moonbase.</i>
- 都再三核对过了吧？  - 是的, 故障肯定在月球基地上

90
00:14:52,014 --> 00:14:54,387
Is it possible for you to effect repairs over video?
你有可能通过视频指导完成修复吗？

91
00:14:54,454 --> 00:14:56,445
Provided the fault is not too major.
除非不是什么大故障

92
00:14:56,614 --> 00:15:00,163
- And provided they actually get there with the rocket!
- They'll get there.
- 还得他们乘坐火箭真的能到那儿  - 他们会到那儿的

93
00:15:00,334 --> 00:15:03,804
Why? How do you know? You can't even be sure the rocket's still in one piece!
为什么？你知道知道？你都不能确定那火箭还是不是完整的！

94
00:15:03,974 --> 00:15:05,486
- Miss Kelly! 
- What is it, Brent?
- Kelly 小姐！  - 什么事, Brent？

95
00:15:05,610 --> 00:15:08,686
We've got through. The emergency T-Mat link to Moon Control is activating!</i>
我们接通了．与月球控制中心的 T-Mat 紧急连接正在激活！

96
00:15:08,804 --> 00:15:10,545
Is someone coming through?
有谁过来吗？

97
00:15:10,914 --> 00:15:12,905
<i>No, it's on send.</i>
不, 设定在上传模式了

98
00:15:13,074 --> 00:15:16,225
Moonbase must has managed to make a temporary repair.
月球基地肯定是设法临时修复了部分功能

99
00:15:16,394 --> 00:15:20,224
It's all we need. Brent, have a full emergency kit waiting.
这也够了．Brent, 准备好全套紧急救援设备

100
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:24,492
- I'll join you as soon as possible.
- <i>Yes, Miss Kelly. Standing by.</i>
- 我随后就来   - 好的, Kelly, 

101
00:15:24,774 --> 00:15:26,073
Where do you think you are going?
你觉得你是要去哪儿？

102
00:15:26,134 --> 00:15:28,607
If we can send, it's the only thing I can do.
如果我们能发送, 我就只能做这件事情了

103
00:15:28,674 --> 00:15:30,025
You have no idea what conditions are like up there!
你根本不清楚那上面到底什么情况！

104
00:15:30,094 --> 00:15:32,470
I know all too well what are like down here
但我清楚地知道这下面都是什么情况了

105
00:15:32,634 --> 00:15:34,627
Commander, you've stopped me once.
指挥官, 你阻拦了一次

106
00:15:34,994 --> 00:15:38,873
Please don't try it again, otherwise I shall have to go above your head.
请不要再这样了, 否则我就不得不越级了

107
00:15:40,034 --> 00:15:43,106
- She's after your job, Julian!
- Miss Kelly!
- 她要挑战你的位置了, Julian!  - Kelly 小姐!

108
00:15:58,994 --> 00:16:02,191
(TRILLING TONE)

109
00:16:06,474 --> 00:16:09,086
- Thank heavens you've come!
- What happened?
- 感谢上天你来了!  - 什么情况?

110
00:16:09,154 --> 00:16:13,447
Osgood, it must have been space madness./
He just went berserk! Pretty mad. It was terrifying.
Osgood 他肯定是出现了太空症状了, 他直接就发狂了！太疯狂了, 非常吓人

111
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:16,750
Osgood? But he'd be the last man, I'd have thought!
Osgood？但他应该是最不可能的, 我一直这么以为！

112
00:16:16,914 --> 00:16:19,064
- So did we.
- Where are the others?
- 我们也是  - 其他人在哪儿？

113
00:16:19,234 --> 00:16:22,829
When Osgood fused the controls, Locke tried to stop him.
Osgood 破坏控制系统的时候, Locke 试着阻止他

114
00:16:22,994 --> 00:16:25,588
- Osgood killed him.
- This is fantastic!
- Osgood 杀了他  - 这太不可思议了！

115
00:16:25,754 --> 00:16:29,303
- What about Phipps?
- He was injured too and I put him under sedation.
- Phipps 怎么样了  - 他也受伤了, 我给他用了镇静剂

116
00:16:29,474 --> 00:16:32,068
- And you?
- There's nothing wrong with me.
- 你呢？  - 我没什么事

117
00:16:32,234 --> 00:16:33,713
You look frightened.
你看起来吓坏了

118
00:16:33,874 --> 00:16:36,547
If you'd seen Osgood die, wouldn't you be?
如果你见到 Osgood 死, 你不会吗？

119
00:16:36,714 --> 00:16:39,148
How did he die?
他怎么死的？

120
00:16:39,314 --> 00:16:41,111
His body's outside.
他的尸体在外面

121
00:16:41,274 --> 00:16:42,787
He just went out.
他就那么出去了

122
00:16:42,954 --> 00:16:46,390
Without a pressure suit? I see.
没穿压力服？我明白了

123
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:51,871
Open all control sections and computer links.
打开所有控制区域和电脑连接

124
00:16:54,954 --> 00:16:56,145
Fewsham, what are you doing?
Fewsham, 你在做什么？

125
00:16:56,314 --> 00:16:58,953
I thought I'd best switch off the emergency link.
我觉得我最好还是把紧急连接关闭

126
00:16:59,114 --> 00:17:02,265
- The trouble we've got could easily burn itself out.
- Sensible.
- 我们目前的问题很可能导致它烧坏  - 有道理

127
00:17:02,634 --> 00:17:05,843
Anyway, it will prevent Commander Radnor sending up another security guard
而且, 这样也能阻止指挥官 Radnor 派一个安全人员上来

128
00:17:05,914 --> 00:17:07,509
to drag me back to Earth!
把我拖回地球去！

129
00:17:11,454 --> 00:17:15,447
(RASPING WHISPER) The other human is still free. Find him!
另外一个人还在逃, 找到他！

130
00:17:16,314 --> 00:17:19,306
He must not interfere with our plans!
不能让他干扰我们的计划！

131
00:17:28,234 --> 00:17:30,671
Hello, Earth Control, this is Moonbase.
哈罗, 地球控制中心, 这里是月球基地

132
00:17:30,734 --> 00:17:33,873
Emergency! Emergency! How do you read me?
紧急状况！紧急状况！你们能听到吗？

133
00:17:37,914 --> 00:17:42,305
Hello, Earth Control, this is Moonbase.
Emergency! Emergency! Can you hear me?
哈罗, 地球控制中心, 这里是月球基地．紧急状况！紧急状况！你们能听到吗？
<i>(part2 ends)</i>

